President Trump visited the Las Vegas Metropolitan Police Department to address the mass shooting that took place on October 1, 2017. He expressed his appreciation for the first responders and law enforcement officers who displayed bravery and courage during the attack. The President also offered condolences to the families of those who lost their lives and wished a speedy recovery to the injured. He emphasized the need for unity and love in the face of such tragedy and praised the heroes who risked their lives to save others. The President concluded by expressing his belief in the resilience of the American people and their ability to overcome together.